WEBVTT

00:00:23.780 --> 00:00:27.460
Reading by Simon Wainwright

00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:44.940
Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ, called to be an apostle, separated unto the gospel of God,

00:00:44.940 --> 00:00:52.400
which he had promised afore by his prophets in the Holy Scriptures,

00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:57.640
concerning his son, Jesus Christ our Lord,

00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:03.520
which was made of the seed of David according to the flesh,

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:11.800
and declared to be the Son of God with power according to the Spirit of holiness

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:15.920
by the resurrection from the dead,

00:01:16.360 --> 00:01:23.500
by whom we have received grace and apostleship for obedience to the faith

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:33.060
among all nations for his name, among whom are ye also the called of Jesus Christ.

00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:37.300
To all that be in Rome, beloved of God,

00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:47.520
called to be saints, grace to you, and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:53.380
First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for you all,

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:57.460
that your faith is spoken of throughout the whole world.

00:01:58.200 --> 00:02:05.380
For God is my witness, whom I serve with my spirit in the gospel of his Son,

00:02:05.380 --> 00:02:11.820
that without ceasing I make mention of you always in my prayers,

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:19.760
making requests if by any means now at length I might have a prosperous journey

00:02:19.760 --> 00:02:23.660
by the will of God to come unto you.

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:31.160
For I long to see you, that I may impart unto you some spiritual gift.

00:02:31.160 --> 00:02:39.380
To the end ye may be established, that is, that I may be comforted together with you

00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:43.480
by the mutual faith, both of you and me.

00:02:44.460 --> 00:02:47.720
Now, I would not have you ignorant, brethren,

00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:52.540
that often times I proposed to come unto you,

00:02:52.660 --> 00:02:59.320
but was let hitherto that I might have some fruit among you.

00:02:59.320 --> 00:03:03.580
Also, even as among other Gentiles,

00:03:04.040 --> 00:03:09.600
I am a debtor both to the Greeks and to the barbarians,

00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:13.640
both to the wise and to the unwise.

00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:20.980
So as much as in me is, I am ready to preach the gospel to you,

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:24.480
that are at Rome also.

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:29.020
For I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ,

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:32.800
for it is the power of God unto salvation

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:35.880
to every one that believeth,

00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:39.920
to the Jew first and also to the Greek.

00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:44.020
For therein is the righteousness of God revealed

00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:46.500
from faith to faith,

00:03:46.980 --> 00:03:48.500
as it is written,

00:03:48.980 --> 00:03:51.480
the just shall live by faith.

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:56.020
For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all,

00:03:56.860 --> 00:04:00.140
ungodliness and unrighteousness of men,

00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:03.680
who hold the truth in unrighteousness.

00:04:04.660 --> 00:04:09.360
Because that which may be known of God is manifest in them,

00:04:09.660 --> 00:04:13.040
for God hath showed it unto them.

00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:16.400
For the invisible things of him

00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:19.840
from the creation of the world are clearly seen,

00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:24.820
being understood by the things that are made,

00:04:25.380 --> 00:04:29.300
even his eternal power and Godhead,

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:32.780
so that they are without excuse.

00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:36.020
Because that when they knew God

00:04:36.020 --> 00:04:39.540
they glorified him not as God,

00:04:40.060 --> 00:04:41.280
neither were thankful,

00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:45.180
but became vain in their imaginations

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:48.500
and their foolish heart was darkened.

00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:51.040
Professing themselves to be wise,

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:52.900
they became fools

00:04:52.900 --> 00:04:57.220
and changed the glory of the uncorruptible God

00:04:57.220 --> 00:05:02.480
into an image made like to corruptible man

00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:05.560
and to birds and four-footed beasts

00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:07.660
and creeping things.

00:05:08.280 --> 00:05:13.640
Wherefore God also gave them up to uncleanness

00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:16.620
through the lust of their own hearts

00:05:16.620 --> 00:05:20.720
to dishonor their own bodies between themselves,

00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:24.300
who changed the truth of God into a lie

00:05:24.600 --> 00:05:27.680
and worshipped and served the creature

00:05:27.680 --> 00:05:29.340
more than the Creator,

00:05:29.960 --> 00:05:32.360
who is blessed forever.

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:33.480
Amen.

00:05:34.460 --> 00:05:37.560
For this cause God gave them up

00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:39.460
unto vile affections,

00:05:39.640 --> 00:05:43.540
for even their women did change the natural use

00:05:43.540 --> 00:05:47.040
into that which is against nature,

00:05:47.540 --> 00:05:49.760
and likewise also the men,

00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:52.960
leaving the natural use of the woman

00:05:52.960 --> 00:05:57.040
burned in their lust one toward another,

00:05:57.420 --> 00:05:59.040
men with men,

00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:02.120
working that which is unseemly

00:06:02.120 --> 00:06:04.020
and receiving in themselves

00:06:04.020 --> 00:06:06.440
that recompense of their error,

00:06:06.780 --> 00:06:08.420
which was meat.

00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:12.300
And, even as they did not like

00:06:12.300 --> 00:06:15.100
to retain God in their knowledge,

00:06:15.520 --> 00:06:20.160
God gave them over to a reprobate mind

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:23.920
to do those things which are not convenient,

00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:27.760
being filled with all unrighteousness,

00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:30.400
fornication, wickedness,

00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:33.320
covetousness, maliciousness,

00:06:33.600 --> 00:06:36.280
full of envy, murder, debate,

00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:39.530
deceit, malignity, whisperers,

00:06:39.530 --> 00:06:42.430
back-biters, haters of God,

00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:45.770
despiteful, proud, boasters,

00:06:46.670 --> 00:06:48.390
inventors of evil things,

00:06:48.890 --> 00:06:50.610
disobedient to parents,

00:06:51.410 --> 00:06:54.650
without understanding, covenant-breakers,

00:06:54.890 --> 00:06:56.450
without natural affection,

00:06:57.310 --> 00:06:59.650
implacable, unmerciful,

00:07:00.210 --> 00:07:02.930
who, knowing the judgment of God,

00:07:03.330 --> 00:07:05.890
that they which commit such things

00:07:06.070 --> 00:07:07.590
are worthy of death,

00:07:07.590 --> 00:07:09.690
not only do the same,

00:07:10.130 --> 00:07:14.710
but have pleasure in them that do them.

00:07:16.310 --> 00:07:20.630
Therefore thou art inexcusable, O man,

00:07:21.030 --> 00:07:24.090
whosoever thou art that judgest.

00:07:24.730 --> 00:07:27.690
For wherein thou judgest another,

00:07:28.390 --> 00:07:31.070
thou condemnest thyself.

00:07:31.430 --> 00:07:35.270
For thou that judgest doest the same things.

00:07:35.270 --> 00:07:39.370
But we are sure that the judgment of God

00:07:39.370 --> 00:07:41.030
is according to truth,

00:07:41.610 --> 00:07:44.250
against them which commit such things.

00:07:44.750 --> 00:07:47.650
And thinkest thou this, O man,

00:07:47.910 --> 00:07:50.590
that judgest them which do such things,

00:07:51.010 --> 00:07:52.490
and doest the same,

00:07:52.930 --> 00:07:55.910
that thou shalt escape the judgment of God?

00:07:56.370 --> 00:08:00.090
Or despisest thou the riches of his goodness

00:08:00.090 --> 00:08:04.010
and forbearance and long-suffering,

00:08:04.010 --> 00:08:06.810
not knowing that the goodness of God

00:08:06.810 --> 00:08:08.710
leadeth thee to repentance?

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:13.930
But after thy hardness and impenitent heart

00:08:13.930 --> 00:08:17.030
treasurest up unto thyself wrath

00:08:17.030 --> 00:08:19.610
against the day of wrath,

00:08:20.230 --> 00:08:24.510
in revelation of the righteous judgment of God,

00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:27.470
who will render to every man

00:08:27.470 --> 00:08:30.050
according to his deeds,

00:08:30.050 --> 00:08:37.530
to them who, by patient continuance in well-doing,

00:08:38.390 --> 00:08:43.290
seek for glory and honor and immortality eternal life,

00:08:43.730 --> 00:08:46.270
but unto them that are contentious

00:08:46.270 --> 00:08:48.450
and do not obey the truth,

00:08:48.790 --> 00:08:53.050
but obey unrighteousness, indignation, and wrath,

00:08:53.870 --> 00:08:57.530
tribulation and anguish upon every soul of man

00:08:57.530 --> 00:09:00.830
that doeth evil of the Jew first

00:09:00.830 --> 00:09:03.660
and also of the Gentile.

00:09:04.530 --> 00:09:08.690
But glory, honor, and peace to every man

00:09:08.690 --> 00:09:11.610
that worketh good to the Jew first

00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:14.530
and also to the Gentile.

00:09:15.130 --> 00:09:18.070
For there is no respect of persons with God.

00:09:18.810 --> 00:09:22.230
For as many as have sinned without law

00:09:22.230 --> 00:09:25.030
shall also perish without law.

00:09:25.030 --> 00:09:29.110
And as many as have sinned in the law

00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:32.370
shall be judged by the law.

00:09:33.110 --> 00:09:36.410
For not the hearers of the law are just before God,

00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:39.650
but the doers of the law shall be justified.

00:09:40.370 --> 00:09:45.030
For when the Gentiles which have not the law

00:09:45.030 --> 00:09:49.370
do by nature the things contained in the law,

00:09:49.810 --> 00:09:54.210
these having not the law are a law unto themselves.

00:09:54.210 --> 00:09:59.610
Which show the work of the law written in their hearts,

00:10:00.130 --> 00:10:04.050
their conscious also bearing witness and their thoughts,

00:10:04.810 --> 00:10:09.870
the meanwhile accusing or else excusing one another.

00:10:10.430 --> 00:10:14.810
In the day when God shall judge the secrets of men

00:10:14.810 --> 00:10:18.590
by Jesus Christ according to my gospel,

00:10:18.590 --> 00:10:22.390
behold, thou art called a Jew,

00:10:23.650 --> 00:10:25.830
and restest in the law,

00:10:26.690 --> 00:10:29.390
and makest thy boast of God,

00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:31.450
and knowest his will,

00:10:31.870 --> 00:10:35.550
and approvest the things that are more excellent

00:10:35.550 --> 00:10:38.210
being instructed out of the law,

00:10:38.710 --> 00:10:43.230
and art confident that thou thyself art a guide of the blind,

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:46.350
a light of them which are in darkness,

00:10:46.350 --> 00:10:48.530
an instructor of the foolish,

00:10:48.870 --> 00:10:53.470
a teacher of babes which has the form of knowledge,

00:10:53.910 --> 00:10:56.650
and of the truth in the law.

00:10:57.390 --> 00:11:00.010
Thou therefore which teachest another

00:11:00.010 --> 00:11:02.310
teachest thou not thyself.

00:11:03.130 --> 00:11:05.750
Thou that preachest a man

00:11:05.750 --> 00:11:08.490
should not steal, dost thou steal?

00:11:09.410 --> 00:11:13.350
Thou that sayest a man should not commit adultery,

00:11:13.350 --> 00:11:17.650
dost thou commit adultery?

00:11:18.430 --> 00:11:23.350
Thou that abhorrest idols, dost thou commit sacrilege?

00:11:24.870 --> 00:11:28.210
Thou that makest thy boast of the law through

00:11:28.210 --> 00:11:32.830
breaking the law dishonest thou God?

00:11:34.250 --> 00:11:38.520
For the name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles

00:11:39.190 --> 00:11:41.650
through you as it is written,

00:11:41.650 --> 00:11:47.790
for circumcision verily profiteth if thou keep the law,

00:11:48.350 --> 00:11:50.930
but if thou be a breaker of the law,

00:11:51.150 --> 00:11:54.970
thy circumcision is made uncircumcision.

00:11:55.990 --> 00:12:01.590
Therefore, if the uncircumcision keep the righteousness of the law,

00:12:01.830 --> 00:12:05.550
shall not his uncircumcision be counted for circumcision?

00:12:06.310 --> 00:12:08.530
And shall not uncircumcision,

00:12:08.530 --> 00:12:12.530
which is by nature if it fulfill the law,

00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:17.930
judge thee, who by the letter and circumcision

00:12:17.930 --> 00:12:20.670
dost transgress the law?

00:12:21.650 --> 00:12:26.350
For he is not a Jew, which is one outwardly,

00:12:26.570 --> 00:12:31.770
neither is that circumcision, which is outward in the flesh,

00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:36.750
but he is a Jew, which is one inwardly,

00:12:36.750 --> 00:12:42.110
and circumcision is that of the heart in the spirit

00:12:42.110 --> 00:12:44.590
and not in the letter,

00:12:45.030 --> 00:12:50.150
whose praise is not of men, but of God.

00:13:34.940 --> 00:13:42.580
What advantage then hath the Jew, or what profit is there of circumcision,

00:13:43.240 --> 00:13:50.440
much every way chiefly because that unto them were committed the oracles of God?

00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:56.800
For what if some did not believe, shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect?

00:13:57.400 --> 00:14:02.260
God forbid, yea, let God be true, but every man a liar,

00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:07.780
as it is written, that thou mightest be justified in thy sayings,

00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:11.420
and mightest overcome when thou art judged.

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:17.240
But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God,

00:14:17.240 --> 00:14:25.280
What shall we say? Is God unrighteous, who taketh vengeance? I speak as a man.

00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:30.180
God forbid, for then how shall God judge the world?

00:14:30.540 --> 00:14:37.280
For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie unto his glory,

00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:41.800
why yet am I also judged as a sinner?

00:14:41.800 --> 00:14:49.380
And not rather, as we be slanderously reported, and as some affirm that we say,

00:14:49.920 --> 00:14:55.880
Let us do evil, that good may come. Whose damnation is just? What then?

00:14:56.360 --> 00:15:00.120
Are we better than they? No, and no wise.

00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:07.640
For we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin.

00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:12.320
As it is written, there is none righteous, no, not one.

00:15:12.740 --> 00:15:17.900
There is none that understandeth, there is none that seeketh after God.

00:15:18.260 --> 00:15:24.760
They are all gone out of the way, they are together, become unprofitable.

00:15:25.020 --> 00:15:28.580
There is none that doeth good, no, not one.

00:15:29.100 --> 00:15:35.940
Their throat is an open sepulcher, with their tongues they have used to see

00:15:35.940 --> 00:15:41.220
The poison of asps is under their lips.

00:15:41.660 --> 00:15:44.420
Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness?

00:15:44.840 --> 00:15:47.240
Their feet are swift to shed blood.

00:15:47.540 --> 00:15:50.460
Destruction and misery are in their ways.

00:15:50.960 --> 00:15:54.740
And the way of peace have they not known.

00:15:55.280 --> 00:15:58.120
There is no fear of God before their eyes.

00:15:58.120 --> 00:16:03.300
Now, we know that what things soever the law saith,

00:16:03.580 --> 00:16:06.680
It saith to them who are under the law,

00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:13.480
That every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may become guilty before God.

00:16:13.920 --> 00:16:20.080
Therefore, by the deeds of the law, there shall no flesh be justified in his sight.

00:16:20.400 --> 00:16:23.620
For by the law is the knowledge of sin.

00:16:23.620 --> 00:16:29.960
But now the righteousness of God without the law is manifested,

00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:33.620
Being witnessed by the law and the prophets.

00:16:34.140 --> 00:16:39.200
Even the righteousness of God, which is by faith of Jesus Christ,

00:16:39.580 --> 00:16:45.600
Unto all and upon all them that believe, for there is no difference.

00:16:46.120 --> 00:16:51.280
For all have sinned and come short of the glory of God,

00:16:51.280 --> 00:16:58.600
Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus,

00:16:58.920 --> 00:17:06.700
Whom God hath set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood,

00:17:06.1000 --> 00:17:16.680
To declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past through the forbearance of God.

00:17:16.680 --> 00:17:21.640
To declare, I say, at this time his righteousness,

00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:28.800
That he might be just and the justifier of him which believeth in Jesus.

00:17:29.440 --> 00:17:33.080
Where is boasting then? It is excluded.

00:17:33.600 --> 00:17:39.420
By what law? Of works? Nay, but by the law of faith.

00:17:39.980 --> 00:17:44.720
Therefore, we conclude that a man is justified

00:17:44.720 --> 00:17:48.280
By faith without the deeds of the law.

00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:51.360
Is he the God of the Jews only?

00:17:51.980 --> 00:17:54.880
Is he not also of the Gentiles?

00:17:55.220 --> 00:17:57.640
Yes, of the Gentiles also.

00:17:58.200 --> 00:18:03.280
Seeing it is one God which shall justify the circumcision by faith

00:18:03.740 --> 00:18:06.900
And the uncircumcision through faith.

00:18:07.300 --> 00:18:10.480
Do we then make void the law through faith?

00:18:10.480 --> 00:18:15.120
God forbid, yea, we establish the law.

00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:23.1000
What shall we say then, that Abraham our father as pertaining to the flesh,

00:18:24.460 --> 00:18:25.140
Have found?

00:18:25.640 --> 00:18:29.700
For if Abraham were justified by works,

00:18:30.380 --> 00:18:34.760
He hath whereof to glory, but not before God.

00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:37.040
For what sayeth the scripture?

00:18:37.640 --> 00:18:42.960
Abraham believed God, and it was counted unto him for righteousness.

00:18:43.780 --> 00:18:50.160
Now, to him that worketh is the reward not reckoned of grace, but of debt.

00:18:50.780 --> 00:18:56.300
But to him that worketh not, but believeth on him that justifieth the ungodly,

00:18:56.740 --> 00:19:00.200
His faith is counted for righteousness,

00:19:00.200 --> 00:19:06.680
Even as David also describeth the blessedness of the man

00:19:06.680 --> 00:19:11.060
Unto whom God imputeth righteousness without works.

00:19:11.760 --> 00:19:17.480
Saying, blessed are they whose iniquities are forgiven and whose sins are covered.

00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:22.420
Blessed is the man to whom the Lord will not impute sin.

00:19:22.420 --> 00:19:26.960
Cometh this blessedness then upon the circumcision only,

00:19:27.440 --> 00:19:30.240
Or upon the uncircumcision also?

00:19:30.940 --> 00:19:35.840
For we say that faith was reckoned to Abraham for righteousness.

00:19:36.660 --> 00:19:43.660
How was it then reckoned when he was in circumcision or in uncircumcision?

00:19:44.220 --> 00:19:47.740
Not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision.

00:19:47.740 --> 00:19:51.300
And he received the sign of circumcision,

00:19:51.780 --> 00:19:58.120
A seal of the righteousness of the faith which he had yet being uncircumcised.

00:19:58.400 --> 00:20:02.160
That he might be the father of all them that believe,

00:20:02.840 --> 00:20:05.420
Though they be not circumcised.

00:20:05.840 --> 00:20:10.600
That righteousness might be imputed unto them also.

00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:17.080
And the father of circumcision to them who are not of the circumcision only,

00:20:17.080 --> 00:20:23.180
But who also walked in the steps of that faith of our father Abraham,

00:20:23.940 --> 00:20:27.580
Which he had being yet uncircumcised.

00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:32.840
For the promise that he should be the heir of the world

00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:37.520
Was not to Abraham or to his seed through the law,

00:20:37.920 --> 00:20:40.460
But through the righteousness of faith.

00:20:40.900 --> 00:20:44.520
For if they which are of the law be heirs,

00:20:44.520 --> 00:20:49.760
Faith is made void and the promise made of non-effect.

00:20:50.400 --> 00:20:52.340
Because the law worketh wrath,

00:20:53.020 --> 00:20:57.340
For where no law is, there is no transgression.

00:20:57.860 --> 00:21:04.460
Therefore it is of faith that it might be by grace to the end.

00:21:04.580 --> 00:21:07.960
The promise might be sure to all the seed,

00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:10.960
Not to that only which is of the law,

00:21:10.960 --> 00:21:15.360
But to that also which is of the faith of Abraham,

00:21:15.860 --> 00:21:17.880
Who is the father of us all.

00:21:19.240 --> 00:21:20.520
As it is written,

00:21:21.120 --> 00:21:24.160
I have made thee a father of many nations,

00:21:24.540 --> 00:21:26.660
Before him whom he believed,

00:21:26.820 --> 00:21:29.240
Even God who quickeneth the dead

00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:34.060
And calleth those things which be not as though they were,

00:21:34.700 --> 00:21:37.500
Who against hope believed in hope

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:41.180
That he might become the father of many nations

00:21:41.180 --> 00:21:43.640
According to that which was spoken,

00:21:44.360 --> 00:21:46.060
So shall thy seed be.

00:21:46.840 --> 00:21:48.960
And being not weak in faith,

00:21:49.340 --> 00:21:52.760
He considered not his own body now dead,

00:21:53.260 --> 00:21:56.400
When he was about an hundred years old,

00:21:56.780 --> 00:21:59.120
Neither yet the deadness of Sarah's womb.

00:21:59.460 --> 00:22:03.1000
He staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief,

00:22:03.1000 --> 00:22:05.940
But was strong in faith,

00:22:06.180 --> 00:22:08.100
Giving glory to God,

00:22:08.460 --> 00:22:12.960
And being fully persuaded that what he had promised

00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:16.280
He was able also to perform.

00:22:17.240 --> 00:22:20.960
And therefore it was imputed to him for righteousness.

00:22:21.820 --> 00:22:25.160
Now, it was not written for his sake alone

00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:27.1000
That it was imputed to him,

00:22:28.420 --> 00:22:30.060
But for us also,

00:22:30.060 --> 00:22:34.300
To whom it shall be imputed if we believe on him

00:22:34.300 --> 00:22:38.740
That raised up Jesus our Lord from the dead,

00:22:39.640 --> 00:22:42.860
Who was delivered for our offenses,

00:22:43.360 --> 00:22:47.900
And was raised again for our justification.

00:23:00.060 --> 00:23:00.120
Thanks for watching!

00:23:04.192 --> 00:23:25.392
5. Therefore, being justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus

00:23:25.392 --> 00:23:32.632
Christ, by whom also we have access by faith into this grace wherein we stand, and rejoice

00:23:32.632 --> 00:23:40.032
in hope of the glory of God. And not only so, but we glory in tribulations also, knowing that

00:23:40.032 --> 00:23:47.012
tribulation worketh patience, and patience experience, and experience hope, and hope maketh

00:23:47.012 --> 00:23:53.152
not ashamed, because the love of God is shed abroad in our hearts by the Holy Ghost which is

00:23:53.152 --> 00:24:01.252
unto us. For when we were yet without strength, in due time Christ died for the ungodly. For

00:24:01.252 --> 00:24:07.592
scarcely for a righteous man will one die, yet peradventure for a good man some would even dare

00:24:07.592 --> 00:24:14.672
to die. But God commendeth his love toward us, in that, while we were yet sinners, Christ died for

00:24:14.672 --> 00:24:21.612
us. Much more than, being now justified by his blood, we shall be saved from wrath through him.

00:24:21.612 --> 00:24:28.592
For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his Son, much more being

00:24:28.592 --> 00:24:36.232
reconciled, we shall be saved by his life. And not only so, but we also joy in God through our

00:24:36.232 --> 00:24:43.892
Lord Jesus Christ, by whom we have now received the atonement. Wherefore, as by one man sin entered

00:24:43.892 --> 00:24:50.652
into the world, and death by sin, and so death passed upon all men, for that all have sinned,

00:24:50.652 --> 00:24:57.592
for until the law, sin was in the world, but sin is not imputed when there is no law. Nevertheless,

00:24:57.792 --> 00:25:03.452
death reigned from Adam to Moses, even over them that had not sinned after the similitude of Adam's

00:25:03.452 --> 00:25:10.032
transgression, who is the figure of him that was to come. But not as the offence, so also is the

00:25:10.032 --> 00:25:16.892
free gift. For if through the offence of one many be dead, much more the grace of God, and the gift

00:25:16.892 --> 00:25:24.792
by grace, which is by one man, Jesus Christ, hath abounded unto many. And not as it was by one that

00:25:24.792 --> 00:25:31.672
sinned, so is the gift. For the judgment was by one to condemnation, but the free gift is of many

00:25:31.672 --> 00:25:39.852
offences unto justification. For if by one man's offence death reigned by one, much more they which

00:25:39.852 --> 00:25:45.792
receive abundance of grace, and of the gift of righteousness, shall reign in life by one, Jesus

00:25:45.792 --> 00:25:52.472
Christ. Therefore, as by the offence of one judgment came upon all men to condemnation,

00:25:53.012 --> 00:25:59.612
even so by the righteousness of one the free gift came upon all men unto justification of life.

00:26:00.312 --> 00:26:06.992
For as by one man's disobedience many were made sinners, so by the obedience of one shall many

00:26:06.992 --> 00:26:14.412
be made righteous. Moreover, the law entered that the offence might abound, but where sin abounded,

00:26:14.412 --> 00:26:18.972
grace did much more abound. That as sin hath reigned unto death,

00:26:19.352 --> 00:26:25.352
even so might grace reign through righteousness unto eternal life by Jesus Christ our Lord.

00:26:26.752 --> 00:26:32.912
What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin that grace may abound?

00:26:33.412 --> 00:26:41.512
God forbid! How shall we, that are dead to sin, live any longer therein? Know ye not that so many

00:26:41.512 --> 00:26:47.492
us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death? Therefore, we are

00:26:47.492 --> 00:26:53.832
buried with him by baptism into death, that like as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory

00:26:53.832 --> 00:27:00.532
of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life. For if we have been planted

00:27:00.532 --> 00:27:06.092
together in the likeness of his death, we shall be also in the likeness of his resurrection.

00:27:06.812 --> 00:27:12.712
Knowing this, that our old man is crucified with him, that the body of sin might be destroyed,

00:27:13.032 --> 00:27:19.892
that henceforth we should not serve sin. For he that is dead is freed from sin. Now,

00:27:19.892 --> 00:27:26.152
if we be dead with Christ, we believe that we shall also live with him. Knowing that Christ

00:27:26.152 --> 00:27:33.592
being raised from the dead, dieth no more, death hath no more dominion over him. For in that he

00:27:33.592 --> 00:27:41.872
died, he died unto sin once, but in that he liveth, he liveth unto God. Likewise, reckon ye also

00:27:41.872 --> 00:27:49.332
yourselves to be dead indeed unto sin, but alive unto God through Jesus Christ our Lord. Let not

00:27:49.332 --> 00:27:55.732
sin therefore reign in your mortal body, that ye should obey it in the lusts thereof. Neither

00:27:55.732 --> 00:28:01.472
yield ye your members as instruments of unrighteousness unto sin, but yield yourselves

00:28:01.472 --> 00:28:07.472
unto God as those that are alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness

00:28:07.472 --> 00:28:15.332
unto God. For sin shall not have dominion over you, for ye are not under the law but under grace.

00:28:16.052 --> 00:28:23.592
What then, shall we sin because we are not under the law but under grace? God forbid. Know ye not

00:28:23.592 --> 00:28:29.752
that to whom ye yield yourselves servants to obey, his servants ye are to whom ye obey,

00:28:29.752 --> 00:28:36.492
whether of sin unto death or of obedience unto righteousness? But God be thanked that ye were

00:28:36.492 --> 00:28:41.892
the servants of sin, but ye have obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine which was delivered

00:28:41.892 --> 00:28:49.652
you. Being then made free from sin, ye became the servants of righteousness. I speak after the manner

00:28:49.652 --> 00:28:55.732
of men because of the infirmity of your flesh, for as ye have yielded your members servants to

00:28:55.732 --> 00:29:02.732
cleanliness and to iniquity unto iniquity, even so now yield your members servants to righteousness

00:29:02.732 --> 00:29:10.432
unto holiness. For when ye were the servants of sin, ye were free from righteousness. What fruit had

00:29:10.432 --> 00:29:17.092
ye then in those things whereof ye are now ashamed? For the end of those things is death. But now being

00:29:17.092 --> 00:29:23.612
made free from sin and become servants to God, ye have your fruit unto holiness and the end

00:29:23.612 --> 00:29:30.172
of everlasting life. For the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life

00:29:30.172 --> 00:29:35.352
through Jesus Christ our Lord.

00:29:59.913 --> 00:30:05.353
Know ye not, brethren, for I speak to them that know the law, how that the law hath dominion

00:30:05.353 --> 00:30:10.973
over a man as long as he liveth? For the woman which hath an husband is bound by the law

00:30:10.973 --> 00:30:16.973
to her husband so long as he liveth. But if the husband be dead, she is loosed from the

00:30:16.973 --> 00:30:23.013
law of her husband. So then if, while her husband liveth, she be married to another

00:30:23.013 --> 00:30:29.213
man, she shall be called an adulteress. But if her husband be dead, she is free from that

00:30:29.213 --> 00:30:35.093
law, so that she is no adulteress, though she be married to another man. Wherefore,

00:30:35.093 --> 00:30:40.713
my brethren, ye also are become dead to the law by the body of Christ, that ye should

00:30:40.713 --> 00:30:45.813
be married to another, even to him who is raised from the dead, that we should bring

00:30:45.813 --> 00:30:51.713
forth fruit unto God. For when we were in the flesh, the motions of sins, which were

00:30:51.713 --> 00:30:58.333
by the law, did work in our members to bring forth fruit unto death. But now we are delivered

00:30:58.333 --> 00:31:03.753
from the law, that being dead wherein we were held, that we should serve in newness

00:31:03.753 --> 00:31:11.173
of spirit, and not in the oldness of the latter. What shall we say then? Is the law sin? God

00:31:11.173 --> 00:31:18.073
forbid! Nay, I had not known sin, but by the law. For I had not known lust, except the

00:31:18.073 --> 00:31:24.553
law had said, Thou shalt not covet. But sin, taking occasion by the commandment, wrought

00:31:24.553 --> 00:31:31.613
in me all manner of concupiscence, for without the law sin was dead. For I was alive without

00:31:31.613 --> 00:31:38.293
the law once, but when the commandment came, sin revived, and I died. And the commandment,

00:31:38.293 --> 00:31:44.633
which was ordained to life, I found to be unto death. For sin, taking occasion by the

00:31:44.633 --> 00:31:51.393
commandment, deceived me, and by it slew me. Wherefore, the law is holy, and the commandment

00:31:51.393 --> 00:31:58.573
holy, and just, and good. Was then that which is good made death unto me? God forbid! But

00:31:58.573 --> 00:32:04.573
sin, that it might appear sin, working death in me by that which is good, that sin by the

00:32:04.573 --> 00:32:10.933
commandment might become exceeding sinful. For we know that the law is spiritual, but

00:32:10.933 --> 00:32:18.353
I am carnal, sold under sin. For that which I do, I allow not. For what I would, that

00:32:18.353 --> 00:32:26.373
do I not. But what I hate, that do I. If then I do that which I would not, I consent unto

00:32:26.373 --> 00:32:33.033
the law that it is good. Now then, it is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in

00:32:33.033 --> 00:32:40.153
me. For I know that in me, that is, in my flesh, dwelleth no good thing. For to will

00:32:40.153 --> 00:32:46.813
is present with me, but how to perform that which is good I find not. For the good that

00:32:46.813 --> 00:32:54.653
I would, I do not. But the evil which I would not, that I do. Now if I do that, I would

00:32:54.653 --> 00:33:02.433
not. It is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in me. I find then a law, that, when

00:33:02.433 --> 00:33:08.793
I would do good, evil is present with me. For I delight in the law of God after the

00:33:08.793 --> 00:33:15.573
inward man. But I see another law in my members, warring against the law of my mind, and bringing

00:33:15.573 --> 00:33:22.513
me into captivity to the law of sin which is in my members. O wretched man that I am,

00:33:22.733 --> 00:33:29.773
who shall deliver me from the body of this death? I thank God through Jesus Christ our Lord. So

00:33:29.773 --> 00:33:35.733
then with the mind I myself serve the law of God, but with the flesh the law of sin.

00:33:37.233 --> 00:33:44.413
8. There is therefore now no condemnation to them which are in Christ Jesus, who walk not

00:33:44.413 --> 00:33:51.073
after the flesh, but after the Spirit. For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus hath made

00:33:51.073 --> 00:33:57.533
me free from the law of sin and death. For what the law could not do, in that it was weak through

00:33:57.533 --> 00:34:05.273
the flesh, God sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful flesh, and for sin, condemned sin in the

00:34:05.273 --> 00:34:11.573
flesh, that the righteousness of the law might be fulfilled in us, who walk not after the flesh,

00:34:11.573 --> 00:34:17.493
but after the Spirit. For they that are after the flesh do mind the things of the flesh,

00:34:17.913 --> 00:34:24.113
but they that are after the Spirit the things of the Spirit. For to be carnally minded is death,

00:34:24.353 --> 00:34:31.353
but to be spiritually minded is life and peace. Because the carnal mind is enmity against God,

00:34:31.573 --> 00:34:38.493
for it is not subject to the law of God, neither indeed can be. So then they that are in the flesh

00:34:38.493 --> 00:34:45.733
cannot please God. But ye are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if so be that the Spirit of

00:34:45.733 --> 00:34:52.953
God dwell in you. Now if any man have not the Spirit of Christ, he is none of his. And if Christ

00:34:52.953 --> 00:35:00.233
be in you, the body is dead because of sin, but the Spirit is life because of righteousness. But

00:35:00.233 --> 00:35:05.853
if the Spirit of him that raised up Jesus from the dead dwell in you, he that raised up Christ

00:35:05.853 --> 00:35:11.653
from the dead shall also quicken your mortal bodies by his Spirit that dwelleth in you.

00:35:12.313 --> 00:35:18.633
Therefore, brethren, we are debtors, not to the flesh, to live after the flesh. For if ye

00:35:18.633 --> 00:35:24.513
live after the flesh ye shall die, but if ye through the Spirit do mortify the deeds of the

00:35:24.513 --> 00:35:32.553
body ye shall live. For as many as are led by the Spirit of God, they are the sons of God. For ye

00:35:32.553 --> 00:35:37.753
have not received the Spirit of bondage again to fear, but ye have received the Spirit of

00:35:37.753 --> 00:35:45.153
adoption whereby we cry Abba Father. The Spirit itself beareth witness with our Spirit that we

00:35:45.153 --> 00:35:52.033
are the children of God. And if children, then heirs, heirs of God and joint heirs with Christ,

00:35:52.413 --> 00:35:59.213
if so be that we suffer with him, that we may be also glorified together. For I reckon that

00:35:59.213 --> 00:36:06.793
present time are not worthy to be compared with the glory which shall be revealed in us. For the

00:36:06.793 --> 00:36:13.073
earnest expectation of the creature waiteth for the manifestation of the sons of God. For the

00:36:13.073 --> 00:36:19.433
creature was made subject to vanity not willingly, but by reason of him who hath subjected the same

00:36:19.433 --> 00:36:25.533
in hope, because the creature itself also shall be delivered from the bondage of corruption into

00:36:25.533 --> 00:36:31.213
the glorious liberty of the children of God. For we know that the whole creation groaneth

00:36:31.213 --> 00:36:39.233
and travaileth in pain together until now. And not only they, but ourselves also, which have the

00:36:39.233 --> 00:36:45.513
firstfruits of the Spirit, even we ourselves groan within ourselves waiting for the adoption,

00:36:45.733 --> 00:36:53.293
to wit, the redemption of our body. For we are saved by hope, but hope that is seen is not hope.

00:36:53.293 --> 00:36:59.993
For what a man seeth, why doth he yet hope for? But if we hope for that we see not,

00:37:00.373 --> 00:37:06.853
then do we with patience wait for it. Likewise the Spirit also helpeth our infirmities,

00:37:07.293 --> 00:37:13.433
for we know not what we should pray for as we ought, but the Spirit itself maketh intercession

00:37:13.433 --> 00:37:19.893
for us with groanings which cannot be uttered. And he that searcheth the hearts knoweth what is

00:37:19.893 --> 00:37:25.633
mind of the Spirit, because he maketh intercession for the saints according to the will of God.

00:37:26.033 --> 00:37:32.413
And we know that all things work together for good to them that love God, to them who are the

00:37:32.413 --> 00:37:38.833
called according to his purpose. For whom he did foreknow, he also did predestinate to be

00:37:38.833 --> 00:37:44.073
conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the firstborn among many brethren.

00:37:44.853 --> 00:37:50.913
Moreover, whom he did predestinate, them he also called, and whom he called,

00:37:51.153 --> 00:37:56.693
them he also justified, and whom he justified, them he also glorified.

00:37:57.353 --> 00:38:03.373
What shall we then say to these things? If God be for us, who can be against us?

00:38:03.893 --> 00:38:08.413
He that spared not his own Son, but delivered him up for us all,

00:38:08.413 --> 00:38:12.633
how shall he not with him also freely give us all things?

00:38:13.413 --> 00:38:18.813
Who shall lay anything to the charge of God's elect? It is God that justifieth.

00:38:19.313 --> 00:38:22.753
Who is he that condemneth? It is Christ that died,

00:38:23.033 --> 00:38:27.293
yea rather, that is risen again, who is even at the right hand of God,

00:38:27.513 --> 00:38:30.293
who also maketh intercession for us.

00:38:30.853 --> 00:38:36.053
Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? Shall tribulation, or distress,

00:38:36.053 --> 00:38:42.713
or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword? As it is written,

00:38:42.953 --> 00:38:48.613
For thy sake we are killed all the day long, we are accounted as sheep for the slaughter.

00:38:49.533 --> 00:38:54.373
Nay, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him that loved us.

00:38:54.793 --> 00:39:00.333
For I am persuaded that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities,

00:39:00.333 --> 00:39:06.193
nor powers, nor things present, nor things to come, nor height, nor depth,

00:39:06.513 --> 00:39:10.993
nor any other creature, shall be able to separate us from the love of God,

00:39:11.213 --> 00:39:16.093
which is in Christ Jesus our Lord.

00:39:41.062 --> 00:39:48.462
9. I say the truth in Christ, I lie not. My conscience also, bearing me witness in the

00:39:48.462 --> 00:40:18.442
Holy Ghost, that I have great heaviness and continual sorrow in my heart. For I could wish that myself were accursed from Christ for my brethren, my kinsmen according to the flesh, who are Israelites, to whom pertaineth the adoption and the glory and the covenants, and the giving of the law and the service of God, and the promises whose are the fathers, and of whom, as concerning the flesh, Christ came.

00:40:22.322 --> 00:40:41.642
10. Not as though the word of God hath taken none effect, for they are not all Israel which are of Israel. Neither, because they are the seed of Abraham, are they all children. But in Isaac shall thy seed be called.

00:40:42.362 --> 00:40:59.562
That is, they which are the children of the flesh, these are not the children of God. But the children of the promise are counted for the seed. For this is the word of promise. At this time will I come, and Sarah shall have a son.

00:41:00.282 --> 00:41:19.742
And not only this, but when Rebekah also had conceived by one, even by our father Isaac. For the children being not yet born, neither having done any good or evil, that the purpose of God according to election might stand, not of works, but of him that calleth.

00:41:20.622 --> 00:41:35.422
It was said unto her, The elder shall serve the younger. As it is written, Jacob have I loved, but Esau have I hated. What shall we say then? Is there unrighteousness with God?

00:41:36.502 --> 00:41:47.902
God forbid. For he saith to Moses, I will have mercy on whom I will have mercy, and I will have compassion on whom I will have compassion.

00:41:48.782 --> 00:41:56.822
So then, it is not of him that willeth, nor of him that runneth, but of God that showeth mercy.

00:41:57.582 --> 00:42:10.722
For the scripture saith unto Pharaoh, Even for this same purpose have I raised thee up, that I might show my power in thee, and that my name might be declared throughout all the earth.

00:42:11.622 --> 00:42:18.382
Therefore hath he mercy on whom he will have mercy, and whom he will he hardeneth.

00:42:19.562 --> 00:42:27.342
Thou wilt say then unto me, Why doth he yet find fault? For who hath resisted his will?

00:42:28.342 --> 00:42:38.622
Nay, but, O man, who art thou that repliest against God? Shall the thing formed say to him that formed it? Why hast thou made me thus?

00:42:39.502 --> 00:42:47.182
Hath not the potter power over the clay, of the same lump to make one vessel unto honor, and another unto dishonor?

00:42:48.062 --> 00:42:58.242
What if God, willing to show his wrath and to make his power known, endured with much long suffering the vessels of wrath fitted to destruction,

00:42:58.842 --> 00:43:06.522
and that he might make known the riches of his glory on the vessels of mercy, which he had afore prepared unto glory,

00:43:06.522 --> 00:43:13.502
even us whom he hath called, not of the Jews only, but also of the Gentiles?

00:43:14.282 --> 00:43:24.342
As he saith also in Hosi, I will call them my people which were not my people, and her beloved which was not beloved.

00:43:25.402 --> 00:43:36.122
And it shall come to pass that in the place where it was said unto them, Ye are not my people, there shall they be called the children of the living God.

00:43:37.502 --> 00:43:40.762
Esaias also crieth concerning Israel.

00:43:41.342 --> 00:43:47.642
Though the number of the children of Israel be as the sand of the sea, a remnant shall be saved.

00:43:48.202 --> 00:43:55.922
For he will finish the work, and cut it short in righteousness, because a short work will the Lord make upon the earth.

00:43:56.482 --> 00:43:59.062
And as Esaias said before,

00:43:59.822 --> 00:44:07.702
Except the Lord of Sabaoth had left us a seed, we had been as Sodom and been made like unto Gomorrah.

00:44:08.942 --> 00:44:18.762
What shall we say then, that the Gentiles which followed not after righteousness have attained to righteousness even the righteousness which is of faith?

00:44:19.392 --> 00:44:26.322
But Israel which followed after the law of righteousness hath not attained the law of righteousness?

00:44:27.342 --> 00:44:28.042
Wherefore?

00:44:28.902 --> 00:44:35.602
Because they sought it not by faith, but, as it were, by the works of the law.

00:44:36.022 --> 00:44:38.702
For they stumbled at that stumbling stone.

00:44:39.082 --> 00:44:40.102
As it is written,

00:44:40.982 --> 00:44:49.982
Behold, I lay in Sion a stumbling stone and a rock of offense, and whosoever believeth on him shall not be ashamed.

00:44:53.322 --> 00:45:00.042
Brethren, my heart's desire and prayer to God for Israel is that they might be saved.

00:45:00.542 --> 00:45:05.382
For I bear them record that they have a zeal of God, but not according to knowledge.

00:45:05.382 --> 00:45:16.822
For they, being ignorant of God's righteousness, and going about to establish their own righteousness, have not submitted themselves unto the righteousness of God.

00:45:17.762 --> 00:45:22.942
For Christ is the end of the law for righteousness to every one that believeth.

00:45:24.202 --> 00:45:32.082
For Moses describeth the righteousness which is of the law, that the man which doeth those things shall live by them.

00:45:32.662 --> 00:45:37.422
But the righteousness which is of faith speaketh on this wise.

00:45:38.522 --> 00:45:45.882
Say not in thine heart, Who shall ascend into heaven, that is, to bring Christ down from above?

00:45:46.782 --> 00:45:52.942
Or, Who shall descend into the deep, that is, to bring up Christ again from the dead?

00:45:53.822 --> 00:45:59.702
But what sayeth it? The word is nigh thee, even in thy mouth and in thy heart,

00:46:00.282 --> 00:46:03.302
that is, the word of faith which we preach,

00:46:03.942 --> 00:46:07.502
that if thou shalt confess with thy mouth the Lord Jesus,

00:46:08.002 --> 00:46:12.022
and shalt believe in thine heart that God hath raised him from the dead,

00:46:12.682 --> 00:46:14.262
thou shalt be saved.

00:46:15.262 --> 00:46:22.062
For with the heart man believeth unto righteousness, and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation.

00:46:23.162 --> 00:46:28.722
For the scripture sayeth, Whosoever believeth on him shall not be ashamed.

00:46:29.642 --> 00:46:32.482
For there is no difference between the Jew and the Greek,

00:46:33.022 --> 00:46:37.662
for the same Lord over all is rich unto all that call upon him.

00:46:38.442 --> 00:46:42.962
For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

00:46:43.942 --> 00:46:48.302
How then shall they call on him in whom they have not believed?

00:46:48.902 --> 00:46:52.762
And how shall they believe in him of whom they have not heard?

00:46:53.442 --> 00:46:55.922
And how shall they hear without a preacher?

00:46:57.042 --> 00:47:00.102
And how shall they preach except they be sent?

00:47:00.642 --> 00:47:05.882
As it is written, how beautiful are the feet of them that preach the gospel of peace

00:47:05.882 --> 00:47:08.682
and bring glad tidings of good things.

00:47:09.322 --> 00:47:12.262
But they have not all obeyed the gospel.

00:47:12.782 --> 00:47:17.262
For Esaias sayeth, Lord, who hath believed our report?

00:47:18.142 --> 00:47:22.842
So then, faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the word of God.

00:47:23.582 --> 00:47:26.182
But I say, have they not heard?

00:47:26.782 --> 00:47:33.222
Yes, verily, their sound went into all the earth, and their words unto the ends of the world.

00:47:34.102 --> 00:47:37.402
But I say, did not Israel know?

00:47:38.262 --> 00:47:45.222
First, Moses sayeth, I will provoke you to jealousy by them that are no people,

00:47:45.222 --> 00:47:48.882
and by a foolish nation I will anger you.

00:47:49.302 --> 00:47:52.142
But Esaias is very bold, and sayeth,

00:47:52.702 --> 00:47:55.242
I was found of them that sought me not,

00:47:55.582 --> 00:47:59.502
I was made manifest unto them that asked not after me.

00:47:59.902 --> 00:48:02.022
But to Israel he sayeth,

00:48:02.582 --> 00:48:08.522
All day long I have stretched forth my hands unto a disobedient and gainsaying people.

00:48:15.242 --> 00:48:16.642
Amen.

00:48:35.744 --> 00:48:42.224
I say, then, Hath God cast away his people?

00:48:42.944 --> 00:48:49.764
God forbid, for I also am an Israelite of the seed of Abraham of the tribe of Benjamin.

00:48:50.724 --> 00:48:54.064
God hath not cast away his people which he foreknew.

00:48:55.024 --> 00:48:57.844
What ye not what the scripture saith of Elias?

00:48:58.484 --> 00:49:02.164
How he maketh intercession to God against Israel, saying,

00:49:02.964 --> 00:49:07.844
Lord, they have killed thy prophets and digged down thine altars,

00:49:07.924 --> 00:49:11.844
and I am left alone, and they seek my life.

00:49:12.564 --> 00:49:16.444
But what saith the answer of God unto him?

00:49:17.304 --> 00:49:23.844
I have reserved to myself seven thousand men who have not bowed the knee to the image of Baal.

00:49:25.184 --> 00:49:31.984
Even so, then, at this present time also, there is a remnant according to the election of grace.

00:49:32.684 --> 00:49:36.784
And if by grace, then is it no more of works.

00:49:37.424 --> 00:49:40.184
Otherwise, grace is no more grace.

00:49:40.884 --> 00:49:44.664
But if it be of works, then it is no more grace.

00:49:45.224 --> 00:49:47.824
Otherwise, work is no more work.

00:49:48.744 --> 00:49:53.744
What, then, Israel hath not obtained that which he seeketh for?

00:49:54.164 --> 00:49:57.704
But the election hath obtained it, and the rest were blinded.

00:49:58.984 --> 00:50:03.764
According, as it is written, God hath given them the spirit of slumber,

00:50:04.224 --> 00:50:08.504
eyes that they should not see, and ears that they should not hear.

00:50:08.504 --> 00:50:10.144
Unto this day.

00:50:11.024 --> 00:50:15.504
And David saith, Let their table be made a snare, and a trap,

00:50:15.644 --> 00:50:18.564
and a stumbling block, and a recompense unto them.

00:50:19.224 --> 00:50:24.724
Let their eyes be darkened, that they may not see, and bow down their back all way.

00:50:25.724 --> 00:50:29.344
I say, then, Have they stumbled that they should fall?

00:50:29.864 --> 00:50:30.804
God forbid.

00:50:31.304 --> 00:50:35.844
But rather, through their fall, salvation is come unto the Gentiles,

00:50:36.324 --> 00:50:38.344
for to provoke them to jealousy.

00:50:39.144 --> 00:50:43.224
Now, if the fall of them be the riches of the world,

00:50:43.684 --> 00:50:47.284
and the diminishing of them the riches of the Gentiles,

00:50:47.784 --> 00:50:49.584
how much more their fullness?

00:50:50.724 --> 00:50:56.364
For I speak to you Gentiles, inasmuch as I am the apostle of the Gentiles,

00:50:56.824 --> 00:51:02.704
I magnify mine office, if by any means I may provoke to emulation

00:51:02.704 --> 00:51:06.344
them which are my flesh, and might save some of them.

00:51:06.944 --> 00:51:11.484
For if the casting away of them be the reconciling of the world,

00:51:12.024 --> 00:51:16.304
what shall the receiving of them be, but life from the dead?

00:51:17.144 --> 00:51:21.424
For if the first fruit be holy, the lump is also holy,

00:51:21.884 --> 00:51:24.884
and if the root be holy, so are the branches.

00:51:25.804 --> 00:51:31.324
And if some of the branches be broken off, and thou, being a wild olive tree,

00:51:31.324 --> 00:51:37.624
Wart graft in among them, and with them partakest of the root and fatness of the olive tree,

00:51:38.184 --> 00:51:39.944
boast not against the branches.

00:51:40.904 --> 00:51:45.444
But if thou boast, thou bearest not the root, but the root thee.

00:51:46.484 --> 00:51:52.524
Thou wilt say, then, the branches were broken off that I might be graft in.

00:51:53.544 --> 00:51:59.404
Well, because of unbelief they were broken off, and thou standest by faith.

00:51:59.944 --> 00:52:05.824
Be not high-minded, but fear, for if God spared not the natural branches,

00:52:06.364 --> 00:52:09.184
take heed lest he also spare not thee.

00:52:10.144 --> 00:52:14.724
Behold, therefore, the goodness and severity of God.

00:52:15.304 --> 00:52:20.304
On them which fell severity, but toward thee goodness,

00:52:20.784 --> 00:52:23.624
if thou continue in his goodness.

00:52:24.344 --> 00:52:27.804
Otherwise, thou also shalt be cut off.

00:52:28.684 --> 00:52:34.844
And they also, if they abide not still in unbelief, shall be graft in,

00:52:35.144 --> 00:52:38.004
for God is able to graft them in again.

00:52:38.704 --> 00:52:43.124
For if thou wert cut out of the olive tree which is wild by nature,

00:52:43.604 --> 00:52:47.764
and wert graft contrary to nature into a good olive tree,

00:52:48.384 --> 00:52:52.104
how much more shall these, which be the natural branches,

00:52:52.784 --> 00:52:55.024
be graft into their own olive tree?

00:52:55.684 --> 00:53:00.344
For I would not, brethren, that ye should be ignorant of this mystery,

00:53:00.824 --> 00:53:03.684
lest ye should be wise in your own conceits.

00:53:04.164 --> 00:53:10.804
That blindness, in part, is happened to Israel until the fullness of the Gentiles become in.

00:53:11.404 --> 00:53:14.644
And so all Israel shall be saved.

00:53:15.004 --> 00:53:19.144
As it is written, there shall come out of Sion the Deliverer,

00:53:19.324 --> 00:53:22.104
and shall turn away ungodliness from Jacob.

00:53:22.104 --> 00:53:27.424
For this is my covenant unto them, when I shall take away their sins.

00:53:28.284 --> 00:53:32.464
As concerning the gospel, they are enemies for your sakes.

00:53:32.844 --> 00:53:37.664
But as touching the election, they are beloved for the Father's sakes.

00:53:38.344 --> 00:53:42.124
For the gifts and calling of God are without repentance.

00:53:43.304 --> 00:53:47.844
For as ye, in times past, have not believed God,

00:53:48.204 --> 00:53:51.804
yet have now obtained mercy through their unbelief,

00:53:52.104 --> 00:53:56.424
even so have these also now not believed,

00:53:56.904 --> 00:54:01.244
that through your mercy they also may obtain mercy.

00:54:02.004 --> 00:54:07.884
For God hath concluded them all in unbelief, that he might have mercy upon all.

00:54:08.744 --> 00:54:14.244
O the depth of the riches, both of the wisdom and knowledge of God!

00:54:14.664 --> 00:54:19.444
How unsearchable are his judgments, and his ways past finding out!

00:54:20.024 --> 00:54:24.424
For who hath known the mind of the Lord, or who hath been his counselor,

00:54:24.984 --> 00:54:30.764
or who hath first given to him, and it shall be recompensed unto him again?

00:54:31.444 --> 00:54:40.024
For of him, and through him, and to him, are all things, to whom be glory forever. Amen.

00:54:42.884 --> 00:54:47.164
I beseech you therefore, brethren, by the mercies of God,

00:54:47.164 --> 00:54:50.924
that ye present your bodies a living sacrifice,

00:54:51.284 --> 00:54:55.524
wholly acceptable unto God, which is your reasonable service.

00:54:56.184 --> 00:55:02.704
And be not conformed to this world, but be ye transformed by the renewing of your mind,

00:55:03.164 --> 00:55:08.284
that ye may prove what is that good and acceptable and perfect will of God.

00:55:08.964 --> 00:55:14.684
For I say, through the grace given unto me, to every man that is among you,

00:55:14.684 --> 00:55:17.924
not to think of himself more highly than he ought to think,

00:55:18.324 --> 00:55:24.204
but to think soberly, according as God hath dealt to every man the measure of faith.

00:55:24.944 --> 00:55:31.004
For as we have many members in one body, and all members have not the same office,

00:55:31.704 --> 00:55:38.704
so we, being many, are one body in Christ, and every one members one of another.

00:55:39.764 --> 00:55:44.124
Having, then, gifts differing according to the grace that is given to us,

00:55:44.124 --> 00:55:48.944
whether prophecy, let us prophesy according to the proportion of faith,

00:55:49.624 --> 00:55:53.004
or ministry, let us wait on our ministering,

00:55:53.424 --> 00:55:58.684
or he that teacheth on teaching, or he that exhorteth on exhortation,

00:55:59.444 --> 00:56:02.404
he that giveth, let him do it with simplicity,

00:56:03.084 --> 00:56:08.784
he that ruleth with diligence, he that showeth mercy with cheerfulness.

00:56:09.584 --> 00:56:17.144
Let love be without dissimilation, abhor that which is evil, cleave to that which is good.

00:56:18.004 --> 00:56:23.964
Be kindly affectioned one to another with brotherly love, in honor, preferring one another,

00:56:24.524 --> 00:56:29.104
not slothful in business, fervent in spirit, serving the Lord,

00:56:29.724 --> 00:56:35.144
rejoicing in hope, patient in tribulation, continuing instant in prayer,

00:56:35.144 --> 00:56:40.124
distributing to the necessity of saints, given to hospitality.

00:56:41.164 --> 00:56:45.024
Bless them which persecute you, bless and curse not.

00:56:45.764 --> 00:56:49.854
Rejoice with them that do rejoice, and weep with them that weep.

00:56:50.764 --> 00:56:55.524
Be of the same mind one toward another, mind not high things,

00:56:55.884 --> 00:57:01.464
but condescend to men of low estate. Be not wise in your own conceits.

00:57:02.604 --> 00:57:09.384
Recompense to no man evil for evil, provide things honest in the sight of all men.

00:57:10.164 --> 00:57:15.804
If it be possible, as much as lieth in you, live peaceably with all men.

00:57:16.764 --> 00:57:24.624
Dearly beloved, avenge not yourselves, but rather give place unto wrath, for it is written,

00:57:24.624 --> 00:57:29.784
Vengeance is mine, I will repay, saith the Lord.

00:57:30.604 --> 00:57:38.164
Therefore, if thine enemy hunger, feed him. If he thirst, give him drink. For in so doing,

00:57:38.504 --> 00:57:46.904
thou shalt heap coals of fire on his head. Be not overcome of evil, but overcome evil with good.

00:57:59.622 --> 00:58:00.262
13.

00:58:15.982 --> 00:58:21.802
Let every soul be subject unto the higher powers, for there is no power but of God.

00:58:21.802 --> 00:58:25.142
The powers that be are ordained of God.

00:58:26.022 --> 00:58:32.902
Whosoever therefore resisteth the power, resisteth the ordinance of God, and they that resist shall

00:58:32.902 --> 00:58:39.762
receive to themselves damnation. For rulers are not a terror to good works, but to the evil.

00:58:40.422 --> 00:58:46.622
Wilt thou then not be afraid of the power? Do that which is good, and thou shalt have praise of the

00:58:46.622 --> 00:58:53.202
name. For he is the minister of God to thee for good. But if thou do that which is evil,

00:58:53.542 --> 00:58:59.222
be afraid, for he beareth not the sword in vain, for he is the minister of God,

00:58:59.542 --> 00:59:06.562
a revenger to execute wrath upon him that doeth evil. Wherefore ye must needs be subject,

00:59:06.782 --> 00:59:13.822
not only for wrath, but also for conscience' sake. For for this cause pay ye tribute also,

00:59:13.822 --> 00:59:18.782
for they are God's ministers, attending continually upon this very thing.

00:59:19.522 --> 00:59:25.902
Render therefore to all their dues, tribute to whom tribute is due, custom to whom custom,

00:59:26.342 --> 00:59:33.002
fear to whom fear, honor to whom honor. O, no man anything but to love one another,

00:59:33.422 --> 00:59:40.022
for he that loveth another hath fulfilled the law. For this thou shalt not commit adultery,

00:59:40.022 --> 00:59:46.942
thou shalt not kill, thou shalt not steal, thou shalt not bear false witness, thou shalt not covet.

00:59:47.402 --> 00:59:52.022
And if there be any other commandment, it is briefly comprehended in this saying,

00:59:52.302 --> 00:59:59.962
namely, thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself. Love worketh no ill to his neighbor, therefore

00:59:59.962 --> 01:00:06.782
love is the fulfilling of the law. And that, knowing the time, that now it is high time to

01:00:06.782 --> 01:00:13.142
wake out of sleep, for now is our salvation nearer than when we believed. The night is

01:00:13.142 --> 01:00:20.362
far spent, the day is at hand. Let us therefore cast off the works of darkness, and let us put

01:00:20.362 --> 01:00:27.382
on the armor of light. Let us walk honestly, as in the day, not in rioting and drunkenness,

01:00:27.662 --> 01:00:35.042
not in chambering and wantonness, not in strife and envying. But put ye on the Lord Jesus Christ,

01:00:35.042 --> 01:00:39.922
and make not provision for the flesh to fulfill the lusts thereof.

01:00:41.102 --> 01:00:48.222
Him that is weak in the faith receive ye, but not to doubtful disputations.

01:00:48.622 --> 01:00:56.122
For one believeth that he may eat all things, another, who is weak, eateth herbs. Let not him

01:00:56.122 --> 01:01:03.002
that eateth despise him that eateth not, and let not him which eateth not judge him that eateth,

01:01:03.002 --> 01:01:10.462
for God hath received him. Who art thou that judgest another man's servant? To his own master

01:01:10.462 --> 01:01:17.082
he standeth or falleth, yea, he shall be holden up, for God is able to make him stand.

01:01:17.922 --> 01:01:24.782
One man esteemeth one day above another, another esteemeth every day alike. Let every man be fully

01:01:24.782 --> 01:01:32.102
persuaded in his own mind. He that regardeth the day regardeth it unto the Lord, and he that

01:01:32.102 --> 01:01:38.662
eateth not the day to the Lord he doth not regard it. He that eateth eateth to the Lord,

01:01:38.942 --> 01:01:46.202
for he giveth God thanks, and he that eateth not to the Lord he eateth not and giveth God thanks.

01:01:46.782 --> 01:01:53.262
For none of us liveth to himself, and no man dieth to himself. For whether we live,

01:01:53.402 --> 01:02:00.642
we live unto the Lord, and whether we die, we die unto the Lord. Whether we live therefore or die,

01:02:00.642 --> 01:02:08.302
we are the Lord's. For to this end Christ both died and rose and revived, that he might be Lord

01:02:08.302 --> 01:02:15.462
both of the dead and living. But why dost thou judge thy brother, or why dost thou set it not

01:02:15.462 --> 01:02:21.642
thy brother? For we shall all stand before the judgment seat of Christ. For it is written,

01:02:21.882 --> 01:02:28.322
As I live saith the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall confess to God.

01:02:28.322 --> 01:02:34.822
So then every one of us shall give account of himself to God. Let us not therefore judge

01:02:34.822 --> 01:02:41.542
one another any more, but judge this rather that no man put a stumbling block or an occasion to fall

01:02:41.542 --> 01:02:48.442
in his brother's way. I know and am persuaded by the Lord Jesus that there is nothing unclean

01:02:48.442 --> 01:02:55.982
of itself, but to him that esteemeth anything to be unclean, to him it is unclean. But if thy

01:02:55.982 --> 01:03:03.142
brother be grieved with thy meat, now walkest thou not charitably, destroy not him with thy meat,

01:03:03.502 --> 01:03:10.922
for whom Christ died. Let not then your good be evil spoken of. For the kingdom of God is not

01:03:10.922 --> 01:03:17.802
meat and drink, but righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Ghost. For he that in these things

01:03:17.802 --> 01:03:24.842
serveth Christ is acceptable to God and approved of men. Let us therefore follow after the things

01:03:24.842 --> 01:03:32.082
which make for peace, and things wherewith one may edify another. For meat destroy not the work

01:03:32.082 --> 01:03:38.602
of God. All things indeed are pure, but it is evil for that man who eateth with offense.

01:03:39.342 --> 01:03:45.442
It is good neither to eat flesh, nor to drink wine, nor anything whereby thy brother stumbleth

01:03:45.442 --> 01:03:53.402
or is offended, or is made weak. Hast thou faith? Have it to thyself before God. Happy is he that

01:03:53.402 --> 01:04:00.002
condemneth not himself in that thing which he alloweth. And he that doubteth is damned if he

01:04:00.002 --> 01:04:06.182
eat, because he eateth not of faith. For whatsoever is not of faith is sin.

